main event: Multiple witnesses reported seeing two luminous, elliptical objects flying in the sky over San Antonio, Texas on January 12 and January 9, 1953.
interesting points: Witnesses observed the objects traveling at high speeds, with one witness reporting them as large as medium-sized aircraft., The objects were initially suspected to be weather balloons, but their high speed and altitude raised questions., Visual observations were made by multiple independent witnesses, contributing to the credibility of the reports., The objects emitted no sound and left no contrails, making their identification challenging., Reports concluded that the sightings remained classified as unidentified due to a lack of physical evidence.
witness description: Civilians and Air Force personnel observing from ground level and vehicles.
